      <h2>How Jacob Can Help With Foreclosure</h2>
      <p>Facing foreclosure is one of the most stressful situations a homeowner can be in. The clock is ticking. But you likely have more options than you think.</p>
      <p>Selling to a local cash buyer is often the fastest, cleanest way to move forward. No repairs. No showings. No waiting 90 days on the MLS. Just a fair offer and a closing date that works for you.</p>

      <h2>What Makes Cash Buyers Different</h2>
      <p>When you list with a Realtor, you're waiting for a buyer to get financing, pass inspections, and not change their mind. When you sell to Jacob, you're selling to the buyer directly — no middleman, no uncertainty.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Cash offer within 24 hours of seeing the property</li>
        <li>No repairs, cleaning, or prep work required</li>
        <li>Close in as little as 7 days</li>
        <li>No commissions, no fees, no closing costs in most cases</li>
        <li>You pick the closing date</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>The Honest Trade-Off</h2>
      <p>A cash offer will typically be below full retail market value. That's the trade-off for speed, certainty, and zero prep costs. But when you factor in what you'd pay in commissions (5-6%), repair costs, carrying costs, and months of waiting — a fair cash offer often puts more money in your pocket than you'd expect.</p>
      <p>Jacob will always give you a straight answer. If the traditional route is better for your situation, he'll tell you.</p>

      <h2>Next Steps</h2>
      <p>Call or text <a href="tel:3168162983"><strong>(316) 816-2983</strong></a> and tell Jacob about your situation. No pressure, no obligation. Just a real conversation.</p>
